,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(412,45,197,'school holidays',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(413,45,198,'great shift, happy girl, nil issues, \nWent to dog park for a walk with Remy, watched a movie and waited for Jude to be home',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(414,45,205,'0700,1100',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(415,45,206,'nil',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(416,45,208,'No',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(417,45,211,'Happy & Content',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(418,45,213,'Breakfast,Morning snack',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(419,45,214,'nil concerns, Isla fed herself with support',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(420,45,215,'Unpack or pack dishwasher,Clothes washed,Washing hung out or in dryer,Change beds, mattress protector, fitted sheet, Lycra sheet,Walk Remy',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(421,45,216,'Hamstring stretch,Side sit',2,'2026-01-21 02:30:29',NULL,1,'final'),(422,45,176,'No',3,'2026-01-27 19:39:41',NULL,1,'final'),(423,45,189,'Ela, Overnight shift Saturday 24/1 9:30 PM - 7 AM',3,'2026-01-27 19:39:41',NULL,1,'final'),(424,45,198,'Overnight notes\n \nIsla was mostly settled through the night. I heard her vocalize at 5 AM, I checked her pull up and changed it as it was full. She settled and went back to sleep shortly after. She woke up again at 6:30, after taking her to the toilet and changing her she had breakfast on her Rifton chair.\n\nJude talked repeatedly (TR) asking for Meggy around 3 AM, he whispered and didn\'t sit up from bed which indicated he was still half asleep. I played white noise and readjusted his Lycra sheet and he went back to sleep with no issues.',3,'2026-01-27 19:39:41',NULL,1,'final'),(425,45,205,'0700',3,'2026-01-27 19:39:41',NULL,1,'final'),(426,45,206,'None',3,'2026-01-27 19:39:41',NULL,1,'final'),(427,45,208,'No',3,'2026-01-27 19:39:41',NULL,1,'final'),(428,45,213,'Breakfast',3,'2026-01-27 19:39:41',NULL,1,'final'),(429,45,176,'No',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(430,45,183,'Need more body wash for the kids',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(431,45,189,'Ela, Monday 26/01 7-1',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(432,45,198,'Isla was awake and having breakfast when we arrived. She had a great morning walking around curl curl and enjoying the sea breeze.\n\nJude woke up around 8 AM, he was happy, had a toilet incident then a shower. He ate breakfast well then headed off to day program.',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(433,45,205,'0700,1100,1300',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(434,45,206,'None',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(435,45,208,'No',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(436,45,211,'Happy & Content',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(437,45,212,'TI\nJude toilet incident (urine went everywhere whilst sitting on the toilet) showered and disinfected area.',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(438,45,213,'Breakfast,Morning snack,Lunch',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(439,45,214,'Isla\'s bottom slid forwards a couple of times on the Rifton chair whilst having breakfast and lunch. I had to readjust her position a couple of times which was tricky because I was on my own.',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(440,45,215,'Unpack or pack dishwasher,Washing hung out or in dryer,Ensure couch protectors clean adn in place, including cushion covers,Prepare Isla\'s thickened fluids and check with IDDSI Funnel,Tidy kitchen, wipe benches and tables',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(441,45,216,'getting up from the ground',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(442,45,219,'0700',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(443,45,220,'Jude 8 AM Risperdal 1ml',4,'2026-01-27 19:47:46',NULL,1,'final'),(444,45,176,'Yes,Type 3,Large',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(445,45,183,'Body wash',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(446,45,189,'Ela, Tuesday 27/01 1-6',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(447,45,198,'Isla BM during morning shift, XL passed easily whilst sitting in the toilet.\n\nIsla had a great afternoon, she enjoyed listening to her favorite songs and engaged beautifully when I sang to her. I washed her hair before Jude arrived home from day program. Sofi and I also trimmed her armpit and pubic hair. She enjoyed some quiet time on the bean bag afterwards.\n\nJude arrived home a bit escalated, we went for a quick swim and had a good chat by the pool which grounded him a bit. Staff from support society mentioned he had 3 toileting incidents during the day (TI).',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(448,45,205,'1300,1530',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(449,45,208,'No',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(450,45,211,'Happy & Content',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(451,45,212,'Isla was a bit impatient when having her lunch, she repeatedly hit the table and me a couple of times between bites.',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(452,45,213,'Lunch,Afternoon snack,Dinner',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(453,45,214,'Bottom sliding forwards whilst sitting on the Rifton chair.',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(454,45,215,'Unpack or pack dishwasher,Washing folded and put away,Tidy kitchen, wipe benches and tables,Tidy house areas that have been used',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(455,45,216,'getting up from the ground',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(456,45,219,'1530',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(457,45,220,'Jude 1 ml Risperdal 4 PM',5,'2026-01-27 19:54:44',NULL,1,'final'),(458,45,176,'Yes,Type 4,Medium',6,'2026-02-01 08:16:55',NULL,1,'final'),(459,45,182,'Great day with Jude, Walked Remy in the afternoon and Jude enjoyed watching other dogs at the park too. Afternoon tea had while out and about.',6,'2026-02-01 08:16:55',NULL,1,'final'),(460,45,183,'Low on body wash',6,'2026-02-01 08:16:55',NULL,1,'final'),(461,45,189,'Esa F',6,'2026-02-01 08:16:55',NULL,1,'final'),(462,45,197,'Bring swimming g